The paper deals with the problem of recovering a spectrally sparse object from a small number of time domain samples, which is a common problem in signal processing and information theory. The paper proposes a novel nonparametric algorithm based on structured matrix completion, which is a popular technique in machine learning and optimization. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.IT (Information Theory), which deals with the fundamental limits of communication and data compression. The paper also involves signal processing and statistical learning, which are covered by cs.SP (Signal Processing) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The algorithm proposed in the paper involves optimization and numerical analysis, which are covered by cs.NA (Numerical Analysis). Finally, the paper involves the analysis of the algorithm's performance and robustness, which are covered by cs.SI (Sound and Image Processing).
